ivardefs.name: authoredOn
ivardefs.desc: When the request transitioned to being actionable.

ivardefs.name: basedOn_
ivardefs.desc: Plan/proposal/order fulfilled by this request.

ivardefs.name: bodySite_
ivardefs.desc: Anatomic location where the procedure should be performed. This is the target site.

ivardefs.name: category_
ivardefs.desc: A code that classifies the procedure for searching, sorting and display purposes (e.g. "Surgical Procedure").

ivardefs.name: code
ivardefs.desc: A code that identifies a particular procedure, diagnostic investigation, or panel of investigations, that have been requested.

ivardefs.name: context
ivardefs.desc: An encounter or episode of care that provides additional information about the healthcare context in which this request is made.

ivardefs.name: definition_
ivardefs.desc: Protocol or definition followed by this request.

ivardefs.name: doNotPerform
ivardefs.desc: Set this to true if the record is saying that the procedure should NOT be performed.

ivardefs.name: identifier_
ivardefs.desc: Identifiers assigned to this order instance by the orderer and/or the receiver and/or order fulfiller.

ivardefs.name: intent
ivardefs.desc: Whether the request is a proposal, plan, an original order or a reflex order.

ivardefs.name: note_
ivardefs.desc: Any other notes and comments made about the service request. For example, letting provider know that "patient hates needles" or other provider instructions.

ivardefs.name: performer
ivardefs.desc: The desired perfomer for doing the diagnostic testing.  For example, the surgeon, dermatopathologist, endoscopist, etc.

ivardefs.name: performerType
ivardefs.desc: Desired type of performer for doing the diagnostic testing.

ivardefs.name: priority
ivardefs.desc: Indicates how quickly the ProcedureRequest should be addressed with respect to other requests.

ivardefs.name: reasonCode_
ivardefs.desc: An explanation or justification for why this diagnostic investigation is being requested in coded or textual form.   This is often for billing purposes.  May relate to the resources referred to in supportingInformation.

ivardefs.name: reasonReference_
ivardefs.desc: Indicates another resource that provides a justification for why this diagnostic investigation is being requested.   May relate to the resources referred to in supportingInformation.

ivardefs.name: relevantHistory_
ivardefs.desc: Key events in the history of the request.

ivardefs.name: replaces_
ivardefs.desc: The request takes the place of the referenced completed or terminated request(s).

ivardefs.name: requester
ivardefs.desc: The individual who initiated the request and has responsibility for its activation.

ivardefs.name: requisition
ivardefs.desc: A shared identifier common to all procedure or diagnostic requests that were authorized more or less simultaneously by a single author, representing the composite or group identifier.

ivardefs.name: specimen_
ivardefs.desc: One or more specimens that the laboratory procedure will use.

ivardefs.name: status
ivardefs.desc: The status of the order.

ivardefs.name: subject
ivardefs.desc: On whom or what the procedure or diagnostic is to be performed. This is usually a human patient, but can also be requested on animals, groups of humans or animals, devices such as dialysis machines, or even locations (typically for environmental scans).
